4724 IEEE INTERNET OF THINGS JOURNAL, VOL. 11, NO. 3, 1 FEBRUARY 2024
TABLE II RELATED WORKS ON ML-BASED SEI METHODS AND DL-BASED SEI METHODS
Fig. 1. Flowchart of the SEI method based on adaptive signal feature embedded KG. The data collection process collects the received RF signal and converts it into sample data in a universal format through preprocessing; the feature extraction process extracts the required features and feeds them into the KG-AFC architecture to achieve AFC and visualization; and finally, the SEI task is implemented based on the feature classification results.
With the fast development of SEI technology, more DLbased methods have been gradually emerging for better performance. To deal with the high computational complexity of deep convolution neural network (DCNN), Gan et al. [32] proposed a DCNN-based SNR sensing adaptive scalable SEI algorithm to improve efficiency while maintaining high accuracy. Wang et al. [5] proposed a novel DL model called real-valued convolution neural network (RVCNN), which has been applied in SEI to directly process complex baseband signals and improve identification performance. What is more, Zhang et al. [33] proposed a multiscale convolution neural network (MSCNN) of three branches with different convolution kernel sizes, which can improve the absolute accuracy by 15% and the relative accuracy by 22% for SEI tasks. Although the above DL-based SEI methods can effectively improve the identification accuracy of the model, it is difficult to achieve the migration of model features, and the portability is relatively poor. In addition, for large-scale data, the above DL-based SEI methods will generate a large amount of computation overhead, which is a problem we need to avoid as much as possible.
C. KG Classification Methods
KG has gained significant identification in the field of data classification. Menglong et al. [34] proposed a semantic thinning method based on KG to analyze the relationship between similar categories in images from the perspective of semantic knowledge. Xiao et al. [35] proposed a model based on the multiview clustering framework to generate the
semantic representation of knowledge elements (i.e., entities/relationships). This model can effectively implement the classification and retrieval of entities. Lan et al. [36] proposed using a large Chinese medical KG to derive medical knowledge, and using graph neural network (GNN) to make the best use of these knowledge, which enhanced the interaction of knowledge and improved the performance of text classification. Huang et al. [37] proposed a graph knowledge transfer mechanism (GKtran) to solve the limited degree of learning from a short text. This method combines the GNN model to achieve effective graph classification by constructing a word weight. Although existing KG classification methods can fully utilize the rich association information between entities, attributes, and relationships for more accurate classification, most of them are processed based on semantic information, which makes it difficult for a single KG classification method to flexibly migrate and expand when facing new fields or tasks.
III. SYSTEM MODEL AND PROBLEM FORMULATION
A. System Model
This article aims to propose a fast and effective SEI method to realize the identification of RF signals in the IIoT environment. As shown in Fig. 1, the SEI system consists of four parts: 1) data collection; 2) feature extraction; 3) KG-AFC architecture; and 4) emitter identification. First, the emitter signal-acquiring device is used to collect the received RF signal and then proceed to data preprocessing. Second, the sample data with a universal format is extracted through a series of
